    return True
```

This function takes a number as input and returns `True` if it is prime or `False` if it is not. It first checks if the number is less than 2, since any number less than 2 cannot be prime. Then it loops through all the numbers from 2 up to (but not including) the input number, checking each one to see if it divides the number evenly. If any of these numbers do divide the input number evenly, then the input number is not prime and the function returns `False`. If none of the numbers divide the input number evenly, then the input number is prime and the function returns `True`.

