Write a function in C++ to count the number of occurrences of a string inside a longer string.
Response: Here is an example function in C++ to count the number of occurrences of a string inside a longer string:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int countOccurrences(std::string longString, std::string shortString) {
    int count = 0;
    size_t pos = 0;
    while ((pos = longString.find(shortString, pos)) != std::string::npos) {
        ++count;
        pos += shortString.length();
    }
    return count;
}

int main() {
    std::string longString = "the quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog";
    std::string shortString = "the";
    int count = countOccurrences(longString, shortString);
    std::cout << "The word \"" << shortString << "\" appears " << count << " times in the string: \"" << longString << "\"" << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

This function takes two string arguments, one for the longer string and one for the string to be searched for. It then uses the `find()` function of the `std::string` class to search for occurrences of the short string within the longer string. It keeps track of the count of occurrences with a counter variable and returns the count at the end.

